This paper deals with generating realistic images of complex visual scenes, which is a problem in computer vision. The paper proposes a novel approach to mitigate issues in generating images from scene graphs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new model that can learn canonical graph representations, which is related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed model, which is related to machine learning and computational learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with scene graphs, which is related to computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper discusses benchmarks such as Visual Genome, COCO, and CLEVR, which are related to natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
